Network - connection between various hosts and how they communicate

hosts - any device with unique IP addresses and MAC address

IP Address - Internet Protocol Address is a unique label listed to each internet connected device on a local (private) connected 
             network and a public (external) network

Router/Gateway - ntwork device acting as a terminal & filter for all traffic flowing in and out of the network

Firewall - software that filters traffic based on preset rules

Port - a number representing end point communication
